[% BLOCK art__my_image %]

[% SET full_url = "${base_path}art/$url" %]
[% SET full_thumb_url = "${base_path}art/$thumb_url" %]

<article class="design">

<header>
<h3 id="[% id %]"><a href="[% full_url %]">[% title %]</a></h3>
</header>

<a href="[% full_url %]"><img
    src="[% full_thumb_url %]" alt="[% thumb_alt %]"
    /></a>

[% content %]

</article>

[% END %]

[% BLOCK common_art__graphics_design %]

<div class="graphic_designs">

<h2 id="graphics">Graphics</h2>

[% WRAPPER art__my_image id = "back-to-my-homepage--second-ver--using-inkscape"
    url = "back-to-my-homepage-2nd-ver/"
    thumb_url = "images/back_to_my_homepage--v2--inkscape.png"
    thumb_alt = "Back to my Homepage Logo Second Version Using Inkscape"
    title = "Back to my Homepage - Second Version Using Inkscape"  %]

<p>
Second version of the “Back to my Homepage” logo resembling the logo of the
film <i>Back to the Future</i>. This time it was done using the open-source
Inkscape vector-graphics editor and some scripts.
</p>

[%- END -%]


[% WRAPPER art__my_image id = "back-to-my-homepage"
    url = "bk2hp/"
    thumb_url = "images/bk2hp_old.png"
    thumb_alt = "Back to my Homepage (Like Back to the Future)"
    title = "Back to my Homepage"  %]

<p>
The first incarnation of the “Back to my Homepage” image. Many similar images
were popular in ye olde web, but
this time it is modelled like the logo of the film <i>Back to the Future</i>.
</p>

[%- END -%]

